---
// src/pages/terms.astro
// Mirrors the Dog Gone Nails terms structure, adapted for Clean: dog grooming
// service, the Hurricane Bath card-on-file billing (card charged the day before,
// non-refundable inside 24 hours, two-tap cancel), plus the legacy in-person
// Square reality. Business mailing address is a single drop-in pending iPostal1.
import Legal from '../layouts/Legal.astro';
---

<Legal title="Terms of Service" updatedAt="June 2026" description="The terms that govern Dog Gone Clean service.">
  <h2>Identity and Service</h2>
  <p>
    Dog Gone Clean is a mobile dog grooming service operated as a sole
    proprietorship by Paul Nickerson.
  </p>

  <h2>Payment Terms</h2>
  <p>
    For recurring Hurricane Bath service, a card on file is required to book and
    is charged the day before each scheduled appointment, at the 24-hour mark,
    never sooner. If the charge fails, the system notifies you immediately. If
    payment is not resolved within 12 hours of the failure notification, the
    appointment is automatically cancelled. Our operators do not travel to
    unpaid appointments. Legacy full groom clients pay in person at the
    appointment by card, cash, or mobile wallet through Square.
  </p>

  <h2>Cancellation and Refund Policy</h2>
  <p>
    Think of your appointment like a concert ticket. Outside of 24 hours before
    an appointment, you may cancel or reschedule without charge. Inside 24
    hours, the appointment time is reserved for you and is non-refundable. You
    may cancel a recurring series at any time, in two taps, from your client
    portal.
  </p>

  <h2>Photos and Media</h2>
  <p>
    We may take photos or video during appointments. Photos we take are our
    property and may be used on our website, social media, or other business
    purposes at our discretion. Clients may raise specific concerns in writing
    and we will take reasonable steps to accommodate going forward but make no
    guarantees.
  </p>

  <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
  <p>
    To the fullest extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim
    arising from your use of our service is limited to the amount you paid for
    the specific appointment in question.
  </p>

  <h2>Governing Law</h2>
  <p>
    These terms are governed by Florida law. Any disputes will be handled in
    Marion County, Florida.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact Information</h2>
  <p>
    Dog Gone Clean<br />
    [mailing address added after iPostal1 setup]<br />
    service@doggoneclean.us
  </p>
</Legal>
